	   <tr>
			<td>
				<div class="header">How do I sign up?</div>
					<div class="sub-header"> When logged in to the HBO network, click the purple globe <img src="http://hbonet.homebox.com/bizservices/img/globe_updated.png" alt="img-globe"/> on your desktop’s taskbar, or <a target="_blank" href="https://alerts4.athoc.com/HBOss">visit the self-service portal</a> (best experienced on your Internet Explorer browser), where you can update your personal contact information by clicking on <i>My Profile</i>.	   </div>
			</td>
	   </tr>
	   <tr>
			<td>
				<div class="header">Do I have to sign up?</div>
					<div class="sub-header">Participation is voluntary, but be assured that all personal information is kept strictly confidential and will only be used to contact you in an emergency. HBO information (e.g., office phone, HBO mobile phone, HBO email) will be entered into the system automatically; if you do not provide any personal contact information, you could be uninformed of an emergency after-hours.	   </div>
			</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>
				<div class="header">What information is requested?</div>
					<div class="sub-header">The effectiveness of the system is dependent on you. The more personal contact points provided, the better chance you have to receive a message in a crisis or emergency. You have the ability to add the following contact points: personal cell phone (SMS included), home phone, alternate phone, personal email and alternate email.	   </div>
			</td>
	   </tr>
	   <tr>
			<td>
				<div class="header">How do personal contacts provided for WarnerMedia Alerts differ from information I may have provided in Workday?</div>
